  { name: "Pink Floyd - Dark Side of the Moon", price: 23.49, image_url: "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/61hw9WloObL._SL1500_.jpg", description: "PINK FLOYD / DARK SIDE OF MOON - Vinyl LP. The Dark Side of the Moon is the eighth album by the English rock band Pink Floyd. Originally released on 1 March 1973, on the label Harvest, it built on ideas explored in the band's earlier recordings and live shows, but departs from instrumental thematic by founding member Syd Barrett. The album explores themes including conflict, greed, the passage of time, and mental illness, the latter partly inspired by Barrett's deteriorating mental state." },
